title.narrative: Incentivising Economic Reform: Budget Support and Associated Technical Assistance 2019-2022

description.narrative:
NZ will invest in support for Kiribati’s ongoing economic reform agenda, in coordination with the World Bank, Asian Development Bank, Australia and the European Union. The Economic Reform Plan is made up of the government’s priority economic policy and governance reforms. Specific policy areas include:
  • Improve public financial management;
  • Improve the management of public assets and liabilities;
  • Improve the environment for private sector-led growth; and
  • Boost human capital development
